A host had marched out of the city of Freeport to meet the Dervish mounted in the Common Lands.  Vaghris and his wife were caught in the crossfire.<br>
<br>
   He held her hand, guiding her through the field; trying to avoid major skirmishes.  A wild horse, with its rider probably slain, rode past them both and knocked Kodami to the ground.  Vaghris lost sight of where she was after her fall and panicked; he looked fervently for his love amidst the bodies and the battle torn field.  His eyes searched for her, and they found her, trying to get up from where she had fallen.  She got up and had a bit of blood running from the corner of her mouth.  Vaghris reached a hand out to her which she hurriedly grabbed.  Her hold didn’t last long.  A man had snuck up behind her and grabbed her by her long white hair.  With an impish grin on his face, he thrust a short sword through her back. NO…no…Kodami, please…I promised I wouldn’t hurt you…please…<br>
  <br>
   The point of the sword could be seen emerging from her chest; the blade a deep, bloody red.  Her scream could be heard for miles beyond the battle ground; the pain and agony, even Vaghris could seem to feel it in his heart.  The attacker let the body slide off his blade and returned to the fray.  Vaghris rushed to his fallen wife’s side, desperate to help her.  <br>
<br>
   Blood ran from her wound, so Vaghris placed his hand there to try to stop the bleeding.<br>
“No Vaghris….mercy…please…the pain...mercy..” she pleaded to him.<br>
Her eyes closed and he felt her life slip from his grasp.  Her hand fell from his, plummeting to the ground…<br>
<br>
 <br>
   With a thud Vaghris awoke from his painful sleep, sweating and breathing heavily.  He was back in his home in Neriak, resting on his small stuffed couch in the common area.  He got up in a hurry, rushing about the house, yell for his wife, “Kodami!! KODAMI!!! Where are you, blast it?!”  He went from room to room, each empty and lonely....<br>
<br>
